About Gabriella Wilde

Gabriella Wilde is an English model and actress whose famous film roles include Constance Bonacieux in The Three Musketeers, Sue Snell in Carrie and Jade Butterfield in Endless Love.

Career

She began her modeling career at the age of 14 after being discovered by iconic model Naomi Campbell whose modeling career saw her pose for magazines such as Vogue, NylonandCosmopolitan. She made her acting debut in the 2009 film St Trinian's 2: The Legend of Fritton's Gold, where she played the character Saffy.

Family Life

She is the daughter of businessman John Anstruther-Gough-Calthorpe and Vanessa Mary Theresa. She has a younger sister named Octavia and five half-siblings. She and Alan Pownall had a son named Sasha Blue Pownall before their marriage in 2014.
